news.title: Jaipur: 18 houses in Lal Dungri caught between JDA and JMC-H
news.para: Lal Dungri residents are in a difficult situation. Jaipur Development Authority and Jaipur Municipal Corporation-Heritage are in conflict. JMC-H issued demolition notices for dilapidated homes. Illegal land excavation weakens home foundations. Residents complain about inaction against land mafia. JDA says they will cordon off the area. JMC-H will demolish homes after seven days if JDA does not respond.

news.title: Over 100 illegal shops razed near Majri Chowk, Panchkula
news.para: In a significant anti-encroachment operation, HSVP and MC officials demolished approximately 100 illegal structures near Majri Chowk, including dhabas and shops. The cleared land will be used to rehabilitate eligible families from Gandhi Colony, where many residents live in slum-like conditions.

news.title: Vasai-Virar civic body suspends assistant municipal commissioner for failing to demolish illegal constructions
news.para: The Vasai-Virar City Municipal Corporation suspended Assistant Municipal Commissioner Ganesh Patil for neglecting his duty to demolish illegal constructions within his jurisdiction. This action follows a promise of a large-scale demolition drive after a building collapse that resulted in multiple fatalities. Patil had previously faced suspension for alleged misuse of tax collections, highlighting a pattern of negligence.

news.title: Mohali development body to issue clearance certificates to allottees, builders
news.para: Gmada is set to host a one-day camp at PUDA Bhawan on Saturday, September 13, to distribute clearance certificates to allottees, promoters, and developers. The initiative aims to streamline processes, address stakeholder issues, and improve service delivery. Officials from various departments will be present to assist applicants and resolve queries, ensuring efficient and convenient service.

news.title: Jaipur unveils draft policy for ‘transit oriented development’ zones
news.para: Jaipur's urban development department has proposed a Transit Oriented Development (TOD) policy to promote mixed-use areas near transit stations. The policy aims to reduce reliance on private vehicles, ease congestion, and encourage smart urban growth by establishing TOD zones within an 800-meter radius of metro, railway, and regional transit stations.

news.title: Consumer forum orders Hyderabad builder to refund buyer for undelivered plot
news.para: The Ranga Reddy District Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission has directed a real estate firm to refund ₹42.04 lakh with interest to a homebuyer. This decision came after the firm failed to deliver a residential plot as promised in a pre-launch project, and a subsequent buy-back cheque was dishonored.

news.title: Haryana government tells RERA to fast-track grievance disposal, tighten monitoring of builders
news.para: Haryana government is pushing for faster resolution of real estate grievances and stricter oversight of developers, addressing the high volume of pending RERA complaints. Authorities are implementing measures like help desks, online tutorials, and mediation cells. The government is also tackling corruption within RERA and assisting in recovery efforts while developers raised concerns about bank account attachments and registration fees.

news.title: BMC invites developers for slum rehabilitation projects on 26 land parcels in Mumbai
news.para: BMC has invited Expressions of Interest from developers for slum rehabilitation projects on 26 civic-owned land parcels, following an inadequate response to a previous call for 64 SRA schemes. Developers will construct saleable units alongside rehab portions, managing the entire process from surveys to maintenance.

news.title: Evergrande liquidators get initial offers for control of property services arm
news.para: Liquidators of China Evergrande Group have received non-binding indicative offers for its majority stake in Evergrande Property Services Group. Final offers are expected by November, attracting interest from state-owned entities like China Overseas Holdings and China Resources Holdings. Evergrande Services' shares surged following the announcement, amidst the ongoing Chinese real estate crisis.

news.title: MIDC issues notices to three developers, PMRDA for traffic hazard in Hinjewadi
news.para: MIDC has issued notices to Gera Developments, Godrej Properties, and VTP Realty due to traffic hazards caused by mud from construction vehicles in Hinjewadi Phase-III. The mud, deposited by vehicles transporting materials, made roads slippery, leading to accidents. Developers are instructed to install tyre wash pits and clean roads daily to prevent further issues.

news.title: Bombay HC dismisses Asian Paints' plea against antitrust inquiry: Sources
news.para: An Indian court has dismissed Asian Paints' plea to halt an antitrust inquiry initiated by the Competition Commission of India. The investigation stems from a complaint by Birla Opus, alleging that Asian Paints abused its dominant market position through dealer incentives.

news.title: NBCC inks pact with RIICO to develop ₹3,700 crore project in Jaipur
news.para: NBCC has partnered with RIICO to develop a Rs 3,700 crore project near Jaipur International Airport. The project involves constructing Rajasthan Mandapam and related infrastructure across 95 acres. NBCC will act as the executing agency, with RIICO providing an initial interest-free advance of Rs 50 crore.

news.title: Over 25,000 buildings without OC in Mumbai to be regularised under new policy: Minister
news.para: Maharashtra government is set to regularize over 25,000 buildings in Mumbai lacking Occupation Certificates (OC) through a new policy, offering relief to numerous residents. The decision, addressing past loopholes and developer errors, allows buildings with technical or administrative lapses to become eligible for OCs. Housing societies are encouraged to apply, with a penalty waiver for early submissions.

news.title: Delhi metro revisits 2011 plan: Dwarka-IFFCO Chowk route back on drawing board; DPR awaited
news.para: Delhi Metro Rail Corporation is reconsidering a plan to extend metro connectivity from Dwarka to Gurgaon, potentially linking Yashobhoomi station to IFFCO Chowk. This would provide seamless access to key employment hubs and the airport. While a previous plan was shelved, a fresh proposal for a 12km corridor is under discussion, alongside another overlapping route.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC issues notice to auction five properties over ₹27 crore property tax dues
news.para: The BMC has announced the auction of five properties, including Hotel Oakwood in Juhu, due to property tax arrears exceeding Rs 27 crore. Defaulters have 21 days to settle their dues to avoid the auction. This action follows a multi-stage process involving penalties, demand notices, and property attachment, ensuring legal compliance before proceeding with the auction.

news.title: Nashik civic body serves notices to three lakh property tax defaulters
news.para: The Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) has issued notices to over 3 lakh property tax defaulters, who collectively owe Rs 400 crore. These defaulters have 15 days to clear their dues, which have accumulated over the past one to six years.

news.title: MDDA cracks down on illegal plotting across over 150 bighas in Dehradun region
news.para: The Mussoorie Dehradun Development Authority (MDDA) has intensified its crackdown on illegal land activities, reclaiming over 150 bighas of illegally plotted land in the past month. The authority also sealed numerous unauthorized multi-story buildings across areas like Bhaniyawala, Haridwar Bypass Road, and Rishikesh.

news.title: No registry or power: How Ghaziabad development body plans to check illegal colonies
news.para: Ghaziabad Development Authority seeks to halt property registrations in unauthorized colonies to curb their growth, citing a recent survey revealing a significant increase. This directive clashes with existing registration laws, but GDA argues it's supported by a 2024 Supreme Court order concerning unauthorized constructions and the necessity of completion certificates for essential services.

news.title: Bengaluru: No OC needed for 1,200 sq ft homes; government eases rules for small plots
news.para: The Karnataka government has exempted individual houses on 30x40 sites (1,200 sqft) within Greater Bengaluru Authority limits from needing an occupancy certificate (OC). This decision, announced Tuesday, applies to ground-plus-two or stilt-plus-three floor constructions. The move aims to reduce red tape for smaller residential projects following concerns about mandatory OCs.
